## Overview
Cross-origin isolation via Service Worker requires a page reload after the SW is installed. This creates a "two-load pattern" where:
- **First visit**: Service Worker installs but COOP/COEP headers not yet applied
- **Second visit**: Cross-origin isolated, SharedArrayBuffer available

This bead implements the detection and UX for handling this pattern gracefully.

## Why This Matters

### Without COI (First Load)
| Feature | Status |
|---------|--------|
| Argon2 parallelism | Single-threaded (~3-9s unlock) |
| SharedArrayBuffer | Not available |
| sqlite-wasm OPFS | Limited functionality |
| Offline unlock | Not available |

### With COI (After Reload)
| Feature | Status |
|---------|--------|
| Argon2 parallelism | Multi-threaded (~1-3s unlock) |
| SharedArrayBuffer | Available |
| sqlite-wasm OPFS | Full support |
| Offline unlock | Cached assets work |

## Detection Logic
```javascript
// Check if we're cross-origin isolated
function isCrossOriginIsolated() {
    return window.crossOriginIsolated === true;
}

// Check if Service Worker is installed and controlling
async function isServiceWorkerActive() {
    if (!('serviceWorker' in navigator)) return false;

    const registration = await navigator.serviceWorker.getRegistration();
    return registration?.active != null;
}

// Check if SharedArrayBuffer is available (definitive test)
function isSharedArrayBufferAvailable() {
    try {
        new SharedArrayBuffer(1);
        return true;
    } catch {
        return false;
    }
}

// Determine current state
async function getCOIState() {
    const swActive = await isServiceWorkerActive();
    const coiEnabled = isCrossOriginIsolated();
    const sabAvailable = isSharedArrayBufferAvailable();

    if (!swActive) {
        return 'SW_INSTALLING';
    }
    if (!coiEnabled || !sabAvailable) {
        return 'NEEDS_RELOAD';
    }
    return 'READY';
}
```

